==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clione
<hw>Cli*o"ne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A genus of naked
pteropods. One species (<spn>Clione papilonacea</spn>), abundant in the
Arctic Ocean, constitutes a part of the food of the Greenland whale. It
is sometimes incorrectly called <altname>Clio</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clip</ent>⟦br⟧
